# hanabi-intelligence-extension environment (WXT reads .env natively). Copy to `.env` to override locally.
#
# The backend origin the extension talks to is selected by BUILD MODE in shared/backend.ts
# (dev → http://127.0.0.1:3000, distribution → the hosted EU URL) and drives both the runtime
# base URL and the manifest host_permissions. There is nothing secret to set for local dev.
#
# The send-queue POSTs captured posts to `/api/ingest` on this origin from the background
# worker, authenticated with the sensor token from onboarding, and retries via the `alarms` API.
#
# The hosted EU origin is a placeholder until the hosted deployment; set it in shared/backend.ts.
# Packaging a distribution (`pnpm zip`) intentionally fails while it is still the placeholder;
# `pnpm build` (used by CI) is unaffected.
